creator: Richard Harding Davis
description:
LibriVox recording of The Men of Zanzibar by Richard Harding Davis.
Read in English by Crln Yldz Ksr
This is the story of Hemingway, who, after a hunting trip in Uganda, settles in Zanzibar for a while to live among the English-speaking expatriate community on that island. While keeping his true identity well to himself, he falls in love with Ms. Polly Adair, the American Belle of the little society. But when he asks her to marry him, it seems that Ms. Adair has a secret... - Summary by Carolin
